{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KaU9BG7YzcMBxPUdtjieXu","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CAYLWt5YYnb8JdUixQApZ5","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"RAY CLUSTER CONFIGURATION AUDIT\nNamespace : ray\nAudit Date: 2026-06-25\nAuditor   : read-only automated inspection (no cluster changes made)\n\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1. WORKER REPLICA COUNT\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  Deployment : ray-worker\n  Current    : 3 replicas (all Ready, revision 2)\n  Baseline   : 2 replicas (per last-applied-configuration + rollback-rehearsal)\n  DEVIATION  : +1 replica (50% scale-up, applied at stage_02)\n  Status     : 3/3 pods Running; 2 workers had 1 restart each (pods\n               ray-worker-84d59898cb-8np8h and -wmdfd) — monitor for stability.\n\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n2. IMAGE VERSIONS\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  ray-head   image : rayproject/ray:2.9.0  (revision 2)\n  ray-worker image : rayproject/ray:2.9.0  (revision 2)\n  Baseline         : rayproject/ray:2.8.0  (per rollback-rehearsal)\n  DEVIATION        : Both components upgraded from 2.8.0 → 2.9.0 at stage_03.\n  Note             : Verify Ray 2.9.0 release notes for breaking API or\n                     serialisation changes before any dependent workloads are\n                     scheduled against this cluster.\n\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n3. RESOURCE REQUESTS / LIMITS\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  ray-head   resources : {} (none set)\n  ray-worker resources : {} (none set)\n  Baseline             : {} (unchanged — was never configured)\n  DEVIATION            : None from prior state, but both deployments remain\n                         without resource constraints, which is non-standard\n                         for production workloads.\n  COMPLIANCE NOTE      : Unset resources mean pods can consume unbounded CPU\n                         and memory on their nodes. Recommend adding explicit\n                         requests/limits (e.g., cpu: 500m/2, memory: 512Mi/2Gi\n                         for head; cpu: 1/2, memory: 1Gi/4Gi per worker) and\n                         a LimitRange or ResourceQuota for the namespace.\n\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n4. EXPOSED SERVICES — ray-head Service\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  Service type : ClusterIP (10.96.3.81) — internal-only, no ExternalIP\n  Ports (current):\n    gcs       : 6379/TCP → pod:6379\n    dashboard : 8265/TCP → pod:8265   ← ADDED at stage_04\n  Baseline ports:\n    gcs       : 6379/TCP → pod:6379   (only port in original spec)\n  DEVIATION  : Dashboard port 8265 added to the Service at stage_04.\n               The ray-head container also changed from\n                 --include-dashboard=false\n               to\n                 --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0\n               making the Ray Dashboard reachable cluster-wide on port 8265.\n  COMPLIANCE NOTE: The Dashboard is ClusterIP (not LoadBalancer/NodePort) so\n               it is not directly reachable from outside the cluster.\n               However, any pod in the cluster can reach it.  Review whether\n               unauthenticated dashboard access is acceptable; consider adding\n               NetworkPolicy to restrict dashboard access to authorised\n               namespaces/pods, and evaluate enabling Ray's built-in\n               authentication/TLS if upgrading to a Ray version that supports it.\n\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n5. ACTIVE CONFIGMAPS\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  kube-root-ca.crt   : Standard Kubernetes cluster CA certificate (auto-injected).\n  rollback-rehearsal : Operator-placed script documenting the three changes\n                       applied in stages 02–04 and the exact kubectl commands\n                       needed to revert them.  Contains no secrets.\n\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n6. SUMMARY OF DEVIATIONS FROM BASELINE\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # | Component       | Attribute          | Baseline            | Current\n  --+-----------------+--------------------+---------------------+------------------\n  1 | ray-worker      | spec.replicas      | 2                   | 3\n  2 | ray-head        | container image    | rayproject/ray:2.8.0| rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n  2 | ray-worker      | container image    | rayproject/ray:2.8.0| rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n  3 | ray-head        | dashboard flag     | --include-dashboard=false | --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0\n  3 | svc/ray-head    | spec.ports         | [gcs:6379]          | [gcs:6379, dashboard:8265]\n  - | ray-head        | resources          | {} (unchanged)      | {} (still unset)\n  - | ray-worker      | resources          | {} (unchanged)      | {} (still unset)\n\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n7. RECOMMENDATIONS\n══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  R1. Set resource requests/limits on both deployments to prevent noisy-neighbour\n      resource exhaustion and to enable the Kubernetes scheduler to make\n      optimal placement decisions.\n  R2. Restrict dashboard access with a NetworkPolicy; consider whether\n      unauthenticated cluster-wide dashboard access meets your security posture.\n  R3. Investigate the 1 restart each on 2 ray-worker pods to confirm they are\n      not indicative of OOM kills or CrashLoopBackOff precursors.\n  R4. Review Ray 2.9.0 changelog for deprecations or breaki